headline: Wealthfront (WLTH) IPO Gets Tepid Response as Stock Rises 1% in Market Debut
summary: The initial public offering (IPO) of robo-advisor Wealthfront drew a tepid response on Wall Street with the company’s stock rising only 1.36% in its market debut. Shares of the innovative wealth management company opened trading on the Nasdaq (NDAQ) under the ticker symbol WLTH at $14 a share and ended the day at $14.19, a modest increase that showed lukewarm interest. headline: How a Push for More IPOs Fueled a Wave of Scams
summary: The U.S. government has tried to address the long decline in stock-exchange listings by relaxing the rules for small public companies.  The quandary is on display now at the Securities and Exchange Commission.  Its chairman,  Paul Atkins,  is pushing to further ease the reporting obligations for many smaller companies under a 2012 statute called the JOBS Act.

headline: 2026 S&P Outlook: Why REITs Could Deliver Both Income And Alpha
summary: The S&P 500 (SP500) is rated a buy, with a projected 2026 target of at least 8,000, driven by AI enthusiasm and anticipated lower rates.
